[Original Upload/Notes:](https://web.archive.org/web/20071027042510/http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/16488 "") Another GG map thats somewhat small simple and full of chaos :D I hope you all enjoy it. - Concept Time: 3 days - Build Time: 31 hours 8 versions :P - Testing: 13 hours 5 versions - Recommend Grav: 600, no higher :P lower is fine, your server in the end. Oh and a note :P heh, forgot to mention this, the teleporters are completely random, and its possible that you'll get the rare event of teleporting right back where you started :P Touching the rotating generator will kill you pretty much instantly, where as getting in the way of some other floating spikes etc will take a few seconds if you stay in the way :P if there are any large problems or glitches that I missed in the many hours of testing please tell me lol, most of the testing was done in the late hours of the night and early ones in the morning. For those who were following the development, sorry about the wait, school was hectic past few days with leaving etc :P but now its done and I should be moving onto other ideas for maps, feel free to suggest any :P

I made the layout of this map last year and had it dev textured. I found it buried under all my other unfinished maps and decided to get this one done.

The center area is a windtunnel that pushes players up into the air. There are 3 floors. CTs start at the top floor. Ts start at the bottom. Hell breaks loose in the middle.

Spawn camping/killing is prevented by a one-way door that cant be fired through from either side.

I hope you guys have fun with this map. I had fun making it.

This is part of a one hour map challenge our group had. Inspired by the rainstorm outside, I created a wet gun game map that has a nice fluid movement between areas. The water intensifies the reflectivity of the textures giving everything in gg_wetworks a smooth almost vinyl look.

I know there are probably things that can be improved, which may be done in a future version, but just keep in mind this was a 1 hour timed challenge to make a map from scratch from a single author. The folks in my studio participated in doing QA etc. on the final map. I posted it here for all of you to enjoy.

I have included both a map thumbnail and a NAV file for bots for your use as well. Have fun.

This is a remake of my original Western map (http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/30506). I made this one much better with more detail, a dust sort of theme, more buildings, a more detailed inside bar, better stairs, much better designed windows with glass (original didn't have glass), better scaled windows and doors, much better ladders, buy zones, many more spawn points (i went a little overboard on the spawn points), much better lighting, more props places strategically in the map, and much more.

Also in this map I didn't put in the bridges that connect the roof tops since I found that to be really annoying in the original map.

The buildings are based off a bar (not a real one) so I used tables, stools and wine shelves to make it look realistic. I also added a second floor to all of the buildings to make gameplay a little more exciting.

And overall, this map would also work Excellent for a deathmatch server, it is large enough to provide great gameplay but small enough that it won't be a challenge to find people. 

try it out and assess, tell me what u think.

This is a remake of my original Western map (http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/30506). I made this one much better with more detail, a dust sort of theme, more buildings, a more detailed inside bar, better stairs, much better designed windows with glass (original didn't have glass), better scaled windows and doors, much better ladders, buy zones, many more spawn points (i went a little overboard on the spawn points), much better lighting, more props places strategically in the map, and much more. 

I originally made this map with a 3d skybox, but with it, I lost 40fps, so I removed it and took out anything that was unnecessary for a gungame map, so everything that involved the 3d skybox was removed.

Also in this map I didn't put in the bridges that connect the roof tops since I found that to be really annoying in the original map. 

The buildings are based off a bar (not a real one) so I used tables, stools and wine shelves to make it look realistic. I also added a second floor to all of the buildings to make gameplay a little more exciting.

And overall, this map would also work Excellent for a deathmatch server, it is large enough to provide great gameplay but small enough that it won't be a challenge to find people. 

Enjoy! assess please.

Name: gg_weir

Release notes: This version is a stripped down version of de_weir, removed decorations, and spread spawns out, changed to a later time of day too, sun is setting. Makes for a great Gungame or Deathmatch map.

Type: GG or DM 50 spawns
Description: Small intense map. Access to high vantage points everywhere and a few small areas with vent access too! 

Build notes: 2 weeks, first time using Hammer (so it's my first map), learned a lot while making this level, and enjoyed doing so. Concentrated on gameplay/balance more then looks, wanted to keep framerate as high as possible for an large outdoor area map.

Enjoy!

**NOTE**
Screenshots are from the DE version, only removed decoration props and changed lighting, also removed radar images to keep file size down for DM or GG.
